The paper discusses signal representation and coding theory, which are topics typically covered in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on pairwise distances and inner products suggests a connection to geometric algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the use of randomized embeddings is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI).
